Divisor Series
\layout Standard

Consider the series 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
M_{d}(x)=(1-x)^{2}\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}x^{n}d(n)\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $d(n)=\sigma_{0}(n)$
\end_inset 

 is the number of divisors of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset 

.
 A graph of this function appears below.
 Special values include 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
4M_{d}(1/2) & = & \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}d(n)/2^{n}\\
 & = & \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{2^{n}-1}\\
 & =\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset 

 
